                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Transverse polarization in H-2(p,n)2P",
                "            reaction for polarized neutron production.",
                " Neutron polarization- 0.35 determined by measurement",
                " of proton polarization- 0.85 and transfer coefficient."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Quasi-monoenergetic beam of neutrons with spin,",
                " flipped upon a flip of proton spin. 1 microA proton",
                " beam current, producing about 1.E+6 neutrons/sec on",
                " target. Neutron beam of about 33 mm diameter at the",
                " target, position 3.3 m downstream from production",
                " target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For neutron energy measurement."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SFLIP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Proton spin flipped every few seconds."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measurement of recoil protons from CH2 converter",
                " downstream of actual target -for separate neutron flux",
                " monitor."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron flux normalization is obtained",
                "from the normalization of the proton beam intensity",
                "provided by the Faraday cup."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " System of Plastic Scintillator deltaE and",
                " E detectors. Each left and right arm:",
                " Thin (1 or 2 mm thick) deltaE detector at 20 or 30 cm",
                " from target followed by array of up to 6 plastic",
                " E-detectors (10cm wide,50cm high,4cm thick) placed at",
                " 150 cm from target.",
                ".Detection of protons recoiling from CH2 target over",
                " range 82deg< ANG-CM < 156deg.",
                ".Detection of scattered neutrons in the range 38deg <",
                " ANG-CM <103deg, employing active liquid scintillation",
                " target.",
                ".Faraday Cup provided proton beam intensity for neutron",
                " flux normalization."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three Multi-wire Proportional Chambers to",
                " repeat measurements in region 107deg < ANG-CM <130deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Active liquid scintillator target (NE235H) in",
                " thin-walled glass cylinder of 5cm diameter and 5cm",
                " height in experiment with scattered neutron detection.",
                " For recoil experiment- CH2 targets (236 and 326 mg/cm2",
                " and high-purity graphite for carbon background",
                " determination."
              ]
            }
          ],
